6. COMMERCIAL USE

Commercial Use is prohibited without a Permission Grant. The following are
explicitly prohibited without one: selling the Software or any derivative;
bundling it with a commercial product or service; using it in a paid or
SaaS offering; monetising it through ads, subscriptions, or any other model.

Corporation use of FDK in any form — including accessing, using, or
distributing the Software, or using it as a library in any Dependent Project
— requires explicit written consent and a valid Permission Grant from the
Author before any use begins. This applies regardless of whether the use is
described as internal, non-commercial, or private.

Individual developers who use FDK as a library to build Dependent Projects
that generate revenue must contact the Author before monetising the Dependent
Project. The terms governing that monetisation are set out in a Permission
Grant and are further governed by the FDK Sublicense in the sublicense/
directory of this repository.

The following is permitted without a Permission Grant: installing the Software
on behalf of a paying customer as a labour service only, provided the Software
is installed unmodified, originates from the official repository, any fee
covers labour only and not the Software itself, and the customer is informed
of its source and authorship before installation is complete.

All Permission Grants for Commercial Use are personal and non-transferable
and may be revoked at any time without notice.

